The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 3: Japanese car maker Isuzu is planning to bring its multi-purpose pick-up vehicle D-Max in the country in the next two years. India is a very important market for us. We have plans to launch our pick-up truck D-Max here in the next two years but it has lots of strong competitors, Isuzu Motors Ltd general manager Tac Shindo said. The company is evaluating the Indian market and carrying out a study to finalise a possible foray, he added.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 3: Bank of Barodas (BoB) executive director V. Santhana raman said the bank might decide to hike its benchmark prime lending rate by 0.5-0.75 per cent. The bank is also expected to look at increasing its deposit rates marginally, he said.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 3: Domestic steel makers today warned that the extension of the moratorium on steel prices beyond August 7 will amount to taking back the sector to an era of controls besides severely hampering the growth of the industry.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 3: Voltas is interested in mid-sized acquisitions in the electro-mechanical segment, Voltas executive vice-president and CFO M.M. Miyajiwala said. The company will look at both overseas and domestic acquisitions.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 3: Industry has lauded Prime Minister Manmohan Singhs government for securing IAEA approval for a safeguard agreement for implementing the India-US nuclear deal.                                                                                                                         
